        <h2 style="text-align:center;font-size: 22px;color:cyan;">Bengal Prawns Curry</h2>
        <img style="padding-left:225px;width:400px;height:400px" src="https://images.slurrp.com/prod/recipe_images/transcribe/main%20course/Chingri-Malai-Curry.webp?impolicy=slurrp-20210601&width=1200&height=675" alt="Bengal Prawns Curry">
        <div id="en">
            <p style="color:#f1860b;font-size:15pt;font-weight:bold;">Ingredients:</p>
            <p style="color:#22facb;font-size:20px">For Marinating the Prawns:</p>
            <ul style="list-style-type:circle">
                <li>250g large prawns, cleaned and deveined</li>
                <li>1/2 teaspoon turmeric powder</li>
                <li>Salt to taste</li>
            </ul>
            <p style="color:#22facb;font-size:20px">For the Gravy:</p>
            <ul style="list-style-type:circle">
                <li>1 cup grated fresh coconut</li>
                <li>1 cup coconut milk</li>
                <li>1 teaspoon ginger paste,1 teaspoon garlic paste</li>
                <li>1 teaspoon cumin powder, 1/2 teaspoon turmeric powder, 1/2 teaspoon red chili powder </li>
                <li>2 tablespoons vegetable oil</li>
                <li>1 onion, finely chopped</li>
                <li>2-3 green chilies, slit</li>
                <li>Salt to taste, Sugar to taste</li>
                <li>Fresh coriander leaves for garnish</li>
            </ul>

            <p style="color:#f1860b;font-size:15pt;font-weight:bold;">Instructions:</p>
            <br /><li style="text-decoration: underline;font-size:18px;list-style-type:none;color:#22facb">1. Marinate the Prawns:</li><ul>
                <li>In a bowl, combine the cleaned prawns with turmeric powder and salt.</li>
                <li>Let them marinate for about 15-20 minutes.</li>

            </ul><br /><li style="text-decoration: underline;font-size:18px;list-style-type:none;color:#22facb">2. Prepare the Coconut Paste:</li><ul>
                <li>In a blender or food processor, blend the grated coconut with a little water to create a smooth paste. Set it aside.</li>
                <li>In the same blender, blend the coconut milk. Set it aside as well.</li>

            </ul><br /><li style="text-decoration: underline;font-size:18px;list-style-type:none;color:#22facb">3. Cook the Prawns:</li><ul>
                <li>Heat oil in a deep pan over medium heat.</li>
                <li>Add the marinated prawns and sauté until they turn pink and opaque. </li>
                <li>Remove them from the pan and set aside.</li>


            </ul><br /><li style="text-decoration: underline;font-size:18px;list-style-type:none;color:#22facb">4. Prepare the Gravy:</li><ul>
                <li>In the same pan, add more oil if needed.</li>
                <li>Add finely chopped onions and green chilies. Sauté until the onions become translucent.</li>

            </ul><br /><li style="text-decoration: underline;font-size:18px;list-style-type:none;color:#22facb">5. Add Spices:</li><ul>
                <li>Add ginger paste and garlic paste. Sauté for a few minutes until the raw smell disappears.</li>
                <li>Add cumin powder, turmeric powder, and red chili powder. Stir well and cook for a couple of minutes.</li>

            </ul><br /><li style="text-decoration: underline;font-size:18px;list-style-type:none;color:#22facb">6.Add Coconut Paste:</li><ul>
                <li>Pour in the prepared coconut paste and stir to combine.</li>
                <li>Cook for a few minutes until the oil starts to separate from the mixture.</li>

            </ul><br /><li style="text-decoration: underline;font-size:18px;list-style-type:none;color:#22facb">7. Add Coconut Milk:</li><ul>
                <li>Pour in the coconut milk and mix well.</li>
                <li>Add salt and sugar to taste. Adjust the sugar to balance the flavors.</li>

            </ul><br /><li style="text-decoration: underline;font-size:18px;list-style-type:none;color:#22facb">8. Add Prawns and Simmer:</li><ul>
                <li>Return the sautéed prawns to the pan and stir to coat them with the coconut gravy.</li>
                <li>Let the Prawns Curry simmer over low heat for about 5-7 minutes, allowing the flavors to meld.</li>

            </ul><br /><li style="text-decoration: underline;font-size:18px;list-style-type:none;color:#22facb">9. Garnish and Serve:</li><ul>
                <li>Garnish with fresh coriander leaves.</li>
                <li>Serve the Prawns Curry hot with steamed rice.</li>

            </ul><p style="color:orange;font-size:20px">Enjoy this creamy and flavorful Bengali prawn curry!</p>
